{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb884f0b1-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s5724b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5724b"},"text":"§ 5724b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Taxes on reimbursements for travel, transportation, and relocation expenses","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb884f0b2-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s5724b/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Under regulations prescribed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5738"},"text":"section 5738 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and to the extent considered necessary and appropriate, as provided therein, appropriations or other funds available to an agency for administrative expenses are available for the reimbursement of substantially all of the Federal, State, and local income taxes incurred by an individual, or by an individual and such individual’s spouse (if filing jointly), for any travel, transportation, or relocation expenses furnished in kind, or for which reimbursement or an allowance is provided (but only to the extent of the expenses paid or incurred). Reimbursements under this subsection shall also include an amount equal to all income taxes for which the individual, or the individual and spouse, as the case may be, would be liable due to the reimbursement for the taxes referred to in the first sentence of this subsection."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb884f0b3-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s5724b/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" For purposes of this section, the term “travel, transportation, or relocation expenses” means all travel, transportation, and relocation expenses reimbursed or furnished in kind pursuant to this subchapter or chapter 41.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb884f0b4-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/151/s118/a/7/A/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–151, § 118(a)(7)(A)(i)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-11-14"},"text":"Nov. 14, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/97/978"},"text":"97 Stat. 978","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/473/tI/s120/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–473, title I, § 120(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1969"},"text":"98 Stat. 1969","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/201/dA/tXVII/s1723/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–201, div. A, title XVII, § 1723(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-09-23"},"text":"Sept. 23, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/2759"},"text":"110 Stat. 2759","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/dA/tXI/s1114/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, div. A, title XI, § 1114(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2019","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/133/1604"},"text":"133 Stat. 1604","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXI/s1121/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XI, § 1121(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/3900"},"text":"134 Stat. 3900","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb884f0b5-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb884f0b6-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb884f0b7-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":" substituted “and relocation expenses reimbursed” for “or relocation expenses reimbursed” and “or chapter 41” for “of chapter 41”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2019—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s1114/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 1114(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “of employees transferred” after “relocation expenses” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s1114/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 1114(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “individual, or by an individual and such individual’s spouse (if filing jointly), for any travel, transportation, or relocation” for “employee, or by an employee and such employee’s spouse (if filing jointly), for any moving or storage” and “individual, or the individual” for “employee”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s1114/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 1114(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (b) and struck out former subsec. (b) which read as follows: “For the purposes of this section, ‘moving or storage expenses’ means travel and transportation expenses (including storage of household goods and personal effects under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5724"},"text":"section 5724 of this title","children":[],"tail":") and other relocation expenses under sections 5724a and 5724c of this title.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/201"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–201","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Under regulations prescribed under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5738"},"text":"section 5738 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” for “Under such regulations as the President may prescribe”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/473"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–473","children":[],"tail":" amended section generally, substituting “reimbursement of substantially all of the Federal, State, and local income taxes” for “reimbursement of all or part of the Federal, State, and city income taxes” and “for which the employee and spouse, as the case may be” for “for which the employee, or the employee and spouse, as the case may be” in subsec. (a) and “5724c” for “5726(c)” in subsec. (b)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb884f0b8-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb884f0b9-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Retroactive Effective Date of 2021 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXI/s1121/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XI, § 1121(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-